tome~
Circle began humbly, as the dream of one man.  The dream to prove that
Magicks are more powerful than mere weapons and armor.  This man,
Arkisbane, was joined by other mages of his day. Together they sought to
increase the influence of magic in the land of Boinga.  To further this
goal they aligned themselves as a clan and purchased a place of refuge and
contemplation.
 
In the year when the great storm passed over the land, Arkisbane was
called away to other lands.  He passed leadership of this new clan to one
whom he deemed worthy.  A time of growth and prosperity ensued.  Circle was
quickly accepted in the land and all began to look to them as wise men and
women. Then one day this leader was called away to other adventures.
 
A period of darkness consumed Circle.  They floated for a time
...without guidance.  Until one day a light renewed itself, and rose up out
of the darkness to bring a new life to the Unending path of the Circle.
Mythorn had a vision.  A new way to govern a clan.  Not by rule of one man
or woman, subject to his or her whims, but rule by a group, a council of
those who had long traveled the Path of the Magicks.  He prayed to the gods
and it was ordained that there shall be four members in this 'innermost'
group of Circle.  For by having four leaders Circle would never again be
without a ruler.  Thus was born the tradition of the Inner Circle.
 
This first Inner Circle was short lived.  Two of the chosen four left
the realms of mortality and clanhood in search of the greater Magicks of
immortality. Four moons passed while Circle was once again ruled by one
man, a man who was a capable and kind leader.  One who still had a dream of
a clan ruled by a group.
 
After the fourth moon grew dim, Mythorn dreamt.  In his dream were
presented to him the names of those who should next guide Circle.  Inner
Circle once again rose into being.  This time cautions were taken to ensure
that there would always be leaders if one or more of the Inner Circle were
called away.  Thus began the Outer Circle. Not officially leaders, but
designated protectors and advisors for younger members.  Circle once again
began to prosper as a clan.  Their ranks grew large and they became a
fearsome force in the land of Boinga.  But still their main purpose was the
study and teaching of Magicks.
 
In the year of the great gold dragon, a shadow passed across Circle.
Some members sold themselves to the dark side and tried to turn the entire
clan to the ways of evil.  But with the guidance of Mojo they were put in
their places, and Circle was once again covered by a holy aura of
protection. During this time of upheaval many wise persons were lost to
the dark side.  Unfortunately none of them could be converted back, and
they were forever banished from the brotherhood.  Another brief period of
disarray ensued while new leaders were chosen to replace those who had
left. But this disarray was short lived, and when new leaders were voted
upon, the doors were once again open for Circle to lead the way in search
of ever greater and more powerful knowledge.
 
May the past serve to guide us in our future.
-Recorded this Day of Ascension in the Year of the Coming.
-With many thinks to the elders for their patient retelling of
the past to this humble servant.
~
