#4404
The Open Courtyard~
The eastern wall of the tower has been removed, and this edge of the tower
opens up into the sky and air.  The floor above is only half-sized, and so
you can see straight into the sky from the courtyard.  An ivy-covered marble
arch leads back towards the interior of the tower.  Against the north wall 
there is a semi-circular fountain with the statue of a great mage in the 
middle.  The water flows out of the mage's outstretched hands cascading down 
forming a watery shield.  The wind blows gently through the courtyard and
you swear you hear the words, "Never ending, ever lasting..."
~
